        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 6:27PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 627 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mission Bend, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Sugar Land, northern Missouri City, Stafford, Katy,
Richmond, Bunker Hill Village, Piney Point Village, Town West, Pecan
Grove, Eldridge / West Oaks, Mission Bend, Spring Branch West,
southern Addicks Park Ten, Meadows Place, Fulshear, Cinco Ranch,
Westwood, Four Corners, Alief, and Westchase.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
